========================================================================
  README (Pyl10n python locale module)                   wjd, nov 2008
========================================================================

  Pyl10n in a python locale module replacement. It intends to complement
gettext in your localization needs by adding setlocale-like
functionality without breaking thread-safety with process-wide setlocale
settings.

Copyright: Walter Doekes at OSSO B.V., 2008,2009.
Licensing: GPLv3, see COPYING for details.


------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Getting Pyl10n
------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Currently, Pyl10n is only available through SVN. Check out the latest
version using subversion. The repository is here:

https://code.osso.nl/svn/pyl10n/trunk/pyl10n

------------------------------------------------------------------------
  Installing Pyl10n
------------------------------------------------------------------------
  There are no installation instructions yet.

  Use pyl10ngen.py to generate pickled locale files from the libc plain
text locale files or get pregenerated files from /pyl10n/trunk/locale.
Import pyl10n in your python application to get the currently available
locale functions.


========================================================================
